history.content:
Hello All,

HKN offers a variety of tutoring services for the student body in EECS courses, including walk-in office hours, previous exam archives, and midterm/final review sessions.

Starting 2/7, HKN is offering hybrid tutoring services daily Monday through Friday from 12 PM to 5 PM at Soda 345, Cory 290 and hkn.mu/ohqueue.  To accommodate different time zones, we will also be offering completely virtual tutoring hours from 8 PM to 10 PM at hkn.mu/ohqueue. 

Similar to some of the lower division classes, we will have an office hours queue website where students can submit tickets for help with classes, conceptual problems, or homework (not projects). Additionally classmates and friends can submit group tickets to review concepts together.

All the information related to HKN's tutoring hours can be found at hkn.mu/tutor and the link for the office hour queue is at hkn.mu/ohqueue.

Looking at past exams is extremely helpful for studying for midterms and finals - previous exams and their corresponding solutions can be found on the HKN exam archive, at hkn.mu/exams. Lastly, we will also be hosting midterm and final review sessions throughout the semester. More information on individual review sessions will be posted approximately 1-2 weeks before the exam on the respective course Piazza.

Thanks,

Tutoring Committee

Eta Kappa Nu
